cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "Agent TraceBench: Reproducible observability, replay, and regression checks for LLM agents"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: 2026-06-30
type: software
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  Agent TraceBench is an open-source, dependency-free Python package for
  representing LLM-agent runs as JSON Lines traces, summarizing latency, token,
  and failure behavior, replaying ordered steps, exporting
  OpenTelemetry-compatible spans, and running regression checks in continuous
  integration.
authors:
  - given-names: Vinay
    family-names: Gupta
    affiliation: Independent Researcher
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0000-0749-6609"
repository-code: "https://github.com/aivinay/agent-tracebench"
url: "https://github.com/aivinay/agent-tracebench"
keywords:
  - large language model agents
  - observability
  - OpenTelemetry
  - performance regression
  - continuous integration
  - reproducibility
